        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 5:34PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM CDT, Doppler radar were tracking strong thunderstorms from
near Mason to Loyal Valley over southern Mason County. The
thunderstorms were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mason, Hedwigs Hill, Loyal Valley, Hilda, Koockville, and Us-
87 Near The Mason-Gillespie County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
